---
/**
 * mvcc-internals-deep-dive · Figure 3 — XID wraparound on the 32-bit circle,
 * and freezing as the defense.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/transactions-isolation/mvcc-internals-deep-dive.html (Level 4 figure).
 * Component, not inline MDX, for the kebab-case SVG attr reason (see Fig1).
 * References marker-end="url(#arwA)", so the red #arwA marker is inlined here
 * in a local <defs> (verbatim from the source defs block) so it resolves
 * standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 220"
        role="img"
        aria-label="32-bit xids live on a circle; roughly 2 billion are past and 2 billion future; as the system burns through 2 billion newer xids an old tuple's xmin starts to look in the future and the row vanishes; freezing marks it visible to all"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="300"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">XIDS ARE 32-BIT, COMPARED ON A CIRCLE</text
            >
            <circle cx="160" cy="120" r="74" fill="none" stroke="#6b675f" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle>
            <!-- half labels -->
            <path d="M 160 46 A 74 74 0 0 1 160 194" fill="#eef5ee" opacity="0.5"></path>
            <path d="M 160 46 A 74 74 0 0 0 160 194" fill="#f7ecea" opacity="0.5"></path>
            <text x="120" y="118" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >~2B "future"</text
            >
            <text x="120" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >invisible</text
            >
            <text x="202" y="118" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >~2B "past"</text
            >
            <text x="202" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#2f5d3a">visible</text>
            <circle cx="160" cy="46" r="4" fill="#7a1f12"></circle><text
                x="160"
                y="40"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                fill="#7a1f12">now</text
            >
            <!-- the danger arrow -->
            <line
                x1="248"
                y1="120"
                x2="296"
                y2="120"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.5"
                marker-end="url(#arwA)"></line>
            <text x="272" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417">+2B xids</text
            >
            <!-- danger box -->
            <rect
                x="300"
                y="48"
                width="288"
                height="64"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f7ecea"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="444"
                y="68"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">WITHOUT freezing</text
            >
            <text x="444" y="85" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >old xmin=100 flips to "in the future"</text
            >
            <text x="444" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >→ tuple vanishes · silent data loss</text
            >
            <!-- fix box -->
            <rect
                x="300"
                y="128"
                width="288"
                height="74"
                rx="9"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="444"
                y="148"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">FREEZING — the defense</text
            >
            <text x="444" y="165" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >VACUUM flags old tuples "committed &amp;</text
            >
            <text x="444" y="179" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >visible to all; ignore xmin" → wrap-immune</text
            >
            <text x="444" y="195" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >anti-wraparound autovacuum @ default 200M age</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Circular comparison is what lets visibility work without an ever-growing counter — and it's
        the landmine. Freezing defuses it.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
